   <mods:abstract>Secretary for Foreign Affairs Livingston discusses American debt and
            American resources, economic motives for France and Spain helping the Americans, and an
            account of victories in Virginia and South Carolina. Livingston warns Jay that DeaneÆs
            letters have been published by Rivington. Material in YESCA cipher gives instructions
            regarding loans and treaties, discussions with Spain, and possible negotiations for
            peace. Some material deciphered by Jay and Richard E. Morris editorial staff. Endorsed
            as received 8 Feb. 1782. Notations on this document in JayÆs Account Book of Letters
            Received indicate that it was received under cover to Casa Major from Jon. Williams at
            Nants, after being forwarded from Boston by Jn. R. Livingston. The document arrived with
            marks of inspection, and was accompanied by copies of articles of capitulation for
            Yorktown, WashingtonÆs letters to Congress of 19 Oct. 1781, letters between General and
            Lord Cornwallis, and 18 newspapers."</mods:abstract>
